TopicTitle: [1.12.X] Kerbal Planetary Base Systems v1.6.15 [28. April 2022]

Articles.Content:
13 minutes ago, Nils277 said:

Is the small tank also missing (e.g. In the VAB) or just the big one?

Well, uh, both of the tanks seems to be in game. I don't really know what's wrong, could it be something in codes?

http://imgur.com/VKwxRP8

17 minutes ago, Hippu said:

Well, uh, both of the tanks seems to be in game. I don't really know what's wrong, could it be something in codes?

http://imgur.com/VKwxRP8

Uhm what? That is REALLY weird. I just checked the config of the tank and its internal name did not change. So it should be there. Do you have other crafts with a big KIS tank installed? If yes do they load? What happens if you restart the game and try to load the vessel again?

I'm a bit confused what might happen there.

Could you also provide the KSP.log file? It logs all the internal (error) messages, might be something useful in there.

46 minutes ago, Nils277 said:

Do you have other crafts with a big KIS tank installed? If yes do they load? What happens if you restart the game and try to load the vessel again?

I didn't have other crafts with that tank so I created a new save in my 1.0.5 backup and made craft with that tank in there and tried to load that into 1.1, and it did load into the game. 

After that, I tried to load the save with that space station and somehow it did load into the game, but if I switch to some other craft there is super much weird glitching, repeating particle effects and random parts disappearing when also camera starts to wonder somewhere far away from everything. I don't even know what is going on.  

Also, here is a picture of said space station that didn't load, and marked with red is the part that disappears, https://imgur.com/KMXFk4T (Probably something wrong with some other mod now?)

30 minutes ago, Hippu said:

I didn't have other crafts with that tank so I created a new save in my 1.0.5 backup and made craft with that tank in there and tried to load that into 1.1, and it did load into the game. 

After that, I tried to load the save with that space station and somehow it did load into the game, but if I switch to some other craft there is super much weird glitching, repeating particle effects and random parts disappearing when also camera starts to wonder somewhere far away from everything. I don't even know what is going on.  

Also, here is a picture of said space station that didn't load, and marked with red is the part that disappears, https://imgur.com/KMXFk4T (Probably something wrong with some other mod now?)

Hmm very weird. Can you load the station again to cause the glitch and afterwards send/post the KSP.log file that is in the same folder as the KSP.exe? I'm sure there will be something logged in there where the weird bug originates from.

As RoverDude and DStaal said, the Algae Container converts mulch + ore into fertilizer. I set the resource rations for this part in a way that it does not take too much mulch and therefore allows a full cycle.
